{"TopicId":215025,"ForumId":119,"TopicTitle":"SAS is literally useless","CreatedByName":"FlazeTheDragon","CreatedById":226996,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T13:21:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"FlazeTheDragon","CreatedById":226996,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T13:21:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike, i get that this is not optimal reaction control placement, but properly tuned \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E P.I.D\u0027s should be able to easily cope with this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrent \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is borderline unusable on most builds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/41SrFgje1ck?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022KSP2 What dat SAS do\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Razor235","CreatedById":16436,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T13:55:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDevs have said the PIDs still need tuning, but it really doesn\u0027t look like it even HAS Proportional control, let alone the other two.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T14:00:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d say it\u0027s just \u0027different\u0027 to what you may be familiar with from KSP1.\u00A0 Try using more stabilisation and/or \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo doubt they still have tweaking and tuning to do too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FlazeTheDragon","CreatedById":226996,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T14:00:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678802134\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002216436\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Razor235\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Razor235 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDevs have said the PIDs still need tuning, but it really doesn\u0027t look like it even HAS Proportional control, let alone the other two.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIve been flying FPV drones for a fair number of years and what im seeing honestly just looks like extremely poorly tuned PID\u0027s. I tried to go in to the config files and see if i can tune them me self, but they use some sort of an auto-tune algorithm which which i sadly couldnt figure out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guess is that Integral is the main culprit, bumping it up would for sure make things a lot better, tho im sure its not as easy as that and more fine-tuning needs to be done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258863\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678802414\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d say it\u0027s just \u0027different\u0027 to what you may be familiar with from KSP1.\u00A0 Try using more stabilisation and/or \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo doubt they still have tweaking and tuning to do too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\nIts deffo very different from KSP1, considering\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ewas actually useful there lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\nAdding\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Edoesnt really change anything since\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eis still controlled by the same PID\u0027s, so you get the same result. And reaction wheels are impossible to use on\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s since they have bugged drag calculations. If i added a single reaction wheel to that\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ethe drag would double. \u002B those reaction wheels would still be controlled by the same poorly \u0027\u0027tuned\u0027\u0027\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\nThe only real solution for more complex builds is to turn off\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ecompletely and just fly everything manually with trim, which is extremely tedious.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-14T14:04:12Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2023 02:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by FlazeTheDragon\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T14:38:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeen this behavior before in KSP1. The torque is being applied at a different angle than expected. It\u0027s simply the model or torque direction is wrong. To counter act this, turn off your reaction wheels in the pods and cores and don\u0027t use the inline stabilizers. Just use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and aerodynamics. This has fixed the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E issues for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-14T14:39:10Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2023 02:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by shdwlrd\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T14:40:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo it\u0027s not \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E that is broken, but reaction wheels?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T14:46:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258875\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678804719\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeen this behavior before in KSP1. The torque is being applied at a different angle than expected. It\u0027s simply the model or torque direction is wrong. To counter act this, turn off your reaction wheels in the pods and cores and don\u0027t use the inline stabilizers. Just use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and aerodynamics. This has fixed the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E issues for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI strangely haven\u2019t had any issues with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E in KSP2. It works perfectly fine for me (other than flappy bird planes at high speed), although now that I think of it I don\u2019t think I used any reaction wheels in any of the builds aside from the one built into the MK3 command pod and the MK1 cockpit.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-14T14:46:35Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2023 02:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by MechBFP\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TackleMcClean","CreatedById":192825,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T14:53:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcuse rookie question - what are \u0022PID\u0022s?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FlazeTheDragon","CreatedById":226996,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T14:54:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258875\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678804719\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeen this behavior before in KSP1. The torque is being applied at a different angle than expected. It\u0027s simply the model or torque direction is wrong. To counter act this, turn off your reaction wheels in the pods and cores and don\u0027t use the inline stabilizers. Just use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and aerodynamics. This has fixed the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E issues for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is a decent work around as long as you have fairly low \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E authority. Building in stronger \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E authority gives fairly similar results, not to mention that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E will waste a lot of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E propellant trying to keep you steady since its very inefficient. That said, having to build in a bunch of thrusters in to an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is pretty rough since \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters have (i think) more drag then they should.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678804845\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002291917\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerikBalm\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, KerikBalm said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo it\u0027s not \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E that is broken, but reaction wheels?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNah, anything that is able to be controlled by \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is busted, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, reaction control wheels and cockpits all use the same PID\u0027s. I only got that 1 inline cockpit in the ship from the vid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258881\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678805591\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192825\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TackleMcClean\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, TackleMcClean said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcuse rookie question - what are \u0022PID\u0022s?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPID\u0027s are basically a fly-by wire\u00A0algorithm that is designed for craft control, like planes, rockets, quadcopters etc. Its basically just a program that is designed to keep the craft stable by knowing when to automatically apply reaction control in any of the 3 (x y z) axis.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-14T14:57:42Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2023 02:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by FlazeTheDragon\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Razor235","CreatedById":16436,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T14:58:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258881\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678805591\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192825\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TackleMcClean\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, TackleMcClean said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcuse rookie question - what are \u0022PID\u0022s?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStands for Proportional Integral Derivative controllers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProportional (position only):\u00A0 The further away I am from my target, the more I push towards it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIntegral (position integrated over time):\u00A0 I look at my past data to see how far I\u0027ve moved over some time relative to where I am now, so I can adjust to smooth and prevent deviation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDerivative (position with respect to time):\u00A0 I look at how fast I am going, so I reduce overshooting at the cost of increasing errors because I don\u0027t see where I actually am.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProperly balancing the three will get you a very smooth, predictable, and responsive behavior.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo much P will cause responses too fast and large for the others to compensate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo much I will cause sluggish response and may not reach the actual steadystate target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo much D will cause excessive wiggling around the steadystate target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-14T14:59:30Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2023 02:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Razor235\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wheehaw Kerman","CreatedById":223516,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T15:20:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe reaction wheels in KSP1 were hugely \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E and extremely unrealistic. \u00A0No saturation, just for starters. \u00A0One of the reasons I liked the Soviet parts from Making History was that they loaned themselves well to more realistic \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E-only builds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP2\u2019s nerfing the reaction wheels is an improvement IMHO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:04:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258900\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678807237\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223516\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wheehaw Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, Wheehaw Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP2\u2019s nerfing the reaction wheels is an improvement IMHO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey aren\u2019t actually nerfed but aren\u2019t working as intended currently it seems like because of the intertial tensor scalar.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wheehaw Kerman","CreatedById":223516,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:17:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258928\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678809843\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184845\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MechBFP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, MechBFP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey aren\u2019t actually nerfed but aren\u2019t working as intended currently it seems like because of the intertial tensor scalar.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHopefully they do actually nerf them a bit. \u00A0The reaction wheels were bit of an immersion breaker. \u00A0Every time I used them I had this nagging thought that I shouldn\u2019t be able to convert electricity to angular moment that easily \u003Cspan\u003E:).\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:21:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCockpits also have \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E reaction wheels. Hope they get nerfed too.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:28:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258864\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678802419\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226996\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FlazeTheDragon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, FlazeTheDragon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdding\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Edoesnt really change anything since\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eis still controlled by the same PID\u0027s, so you get the same result. And reaction wheels are impossible to use on\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s since they have bugged drag calculations. If i added a single reaction wheel to that\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ethe drag would double. \u002B those reaction wheels would still be controlled by the same poorly \u0027\u0027tuned\u0027\u0027\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately, the answer really is to spam \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 Not just a couple of thrusters, but like \u0022moar \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0022.\u00A0 You can also try to mess with the engine gimbal and turn that down a bit for a bit more control.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FlazeTheDragon","CreatedById":226996,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:37:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258955\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678811304\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately, the answer really is to spam \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 Not just a couple of thrusters, but like \u0022moar \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0022.\u00A0 You can also try to mess with the engine gimbal and turn that down a bit for a bit more control.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving powerful \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E leads to the exact same issue since \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E is controlled by the same very poorly tuned PID\u0027s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184845-mechbfp/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022184845\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184845-mechbfp/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@MechBFP\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/223516-wheehaw-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022223516\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/223516-wheehaw-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wheehaw Kerman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225696-cocoscacao/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225696\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225696-cocoscacao/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@cocoscacao\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0If you guys want the game to be more realistic nothing prevents you from simply turning reaction controls off. I feel like needing \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E on every craft would make ksp even harder on new players so its a good system to have for accessibility sake.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wheehaw Kerman","CreatedById":223516,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:40:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258958\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678811835\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226996\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FlazeTheDragon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, FlazeTheDragon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving powerful \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E leads to the exact same issue since \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is controlled by the same very poorly tuned PID\u0027s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184845-mechbfp/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022184845\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184845-mechbfp/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@MechBFP\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/223516-wheehaw-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022223516\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/223516-wheehaw-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wheehaw Kerman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225696-cocoscacao/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225696\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225696-cocoscacao/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@cocoscacao\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0If you guys want the game to be more realistic nothing prevents you from simply turning reaction controls off. I feel like needing \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E on every craft would make ksp even harder on new players so it\u2019s a good system to have for accessibility sake.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u2019t disagree. \u00A0The reaction wheels are a not-terrible easy-mode crutch for new players. \u00A0I\u2019d be fine with not nerfing them all the way to real-world levels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nETA: wow I came across as arrogant there. \u00A0Basically, yeah, you\u2019re right.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-14T16:42:46Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2023 04:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Wheehaw Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:46:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258958\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678811835\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226996\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FlazeTheDragon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, FlazeTheDragon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving powerful \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E leads to the exact same issue since \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is controlled by the same very poorly tuned PID\u0027s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184845-mechbfp/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022184845\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184845-mechbfp/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@MechBFP\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/223516-wheehaw-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022223516\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/223516-wheehaw-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wheehaw Kerman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225696-cocoscacao/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225696\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225696-cocoscacao/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@cocoscacao\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0If you guys want the game to be more realistic nothing prevents you from simply turning reaction controls off. I feel like needing \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E on every craft would make ksp even harder on new players so its a good system to have for accessibility sake.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m using a combination of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E and reaction wheels to control craft in orbit (and in space, in a general sense), and I\u0027m not having issues when doing that.\u00A0 It takes a lot of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters and a lot of monopropellant to deal with it, but it\u0027s working for me.\u00A0 I\u0027d ask if you\u0027ve actually tried using it, but I assume you have?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:46:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/226996-flazethedragon/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022226996\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/226996-flazethedragon/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@FlazeTheDragon\u003C/a\u003E true, but manually setting everything bores me greatly. Maybe they could add that in global difficulty settings.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FlazeTheDragon","CreatedById":226996,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:53:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258965\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678812367\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m using a combination of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and reaction wheels to control craft in orbit (and in space, in a general sense), and I\u0027m not having issues when doing that.\u00A0 It takes a lot of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters and a lot of monopropellant to deal with it, but it\u0027s working for me.\u00A0 I\u0027d ask if you\u0027ve actually tried using it, but I assume you have?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyup, i put \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E on most of my bigger craft that actually need to maneuver outside of chilling in orbit. Id suggest using verner \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E, the small monoprop blocks are honestly only useful for docking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jacob Kerman","CreatedById":223574,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T16:58:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224258945\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678810644\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223516\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wheehaw Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, Wheehaw Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHopefully they do actually nerf them a bit. \u00A0The reaction wheels were bit of an immersion breaker. \u00A0Every time I used them I had this nagging thought that I shouldn\u2019t be able to convert electricity to angular moment that easily \u003Cspan\u003E:).\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHonestly, I\u0027m inclined to agree. Turning a 200-ton ship in orbit in ksp\u0027s physics just by using reaction wheels was pretty weird. Made \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E useless on upper stages and landers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-14T17:13:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe biggest problem with falling back on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E in KSP is that it isn\u0027t precise enough to hold a heading without flopping around wasting fuel, or it doesn\u0027t use just enough fuel to start a turn before waiting until aligned to use just enough more fuel.\u00A0 In short, it\u0027s not smart. Reaction wheels with decent control authority are absolutely necessary to avoid these issues without relying on an experienced user to handle and remember all this stuff. I don\u0027t mind the strength of reaction wheels in KSP2, they seem toned-down from KSP1 (which was ridiculous), although it would be nice to require desaturating them with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E on occasion, I think that would be a good compromise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nE: Plus, I need decent reaction wheels to flip my rover over when the terrain randomly throws it into the air.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-14T17:14:14Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2023 05:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by regex\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}